Potassium Sorbate Solution 40% Market Overview
The global Potassium Sorbate Solution 40% market was valued at approximately USD 534.8 million in 2023 and is projected to reach USD 852.1 million by 2030, growing at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 7.15% during the forecast period from 2024 to 2030. This growth is driven by the increasing demand for natural preservatives across various industries, including food and beverage, pharmaceuticals, and personal care products. Potassium sorbate is widely used for its effectiveness in inhibiting mold, yeast, and fungus growth, thereby extending the shelf life of products. The market's expansion is further supported by the rising consumer preference for clean-label and natural ingredients, as well as advancements in food processing technologies. Additionally, the growing applications of potassium sorbate in personal care and pharmaceutical products contribute to the market's positive outlook.

